HEADWORD: Tropist
<hw>Trop"ist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>tropiste</ets>. See <er>Trope</er>.]</ety> <def>One who deals in
tropes;</def> <specif>specifically,</specif> <def>one who avoids the
literal sense of the language of Scripture by explaining it as mere
tropes and figures of speech.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

